There is an NGN-denominated account




 
HF Markets
Overview
HF Markets Group’s worldwide brand name is HF Markets (formerly HotForex). Nigerian traders’ orders are sent straight to the market without any intervention from the broker.
One of the most popular accounts, the Micro Account, requires a minimum deposit of only 2,000 NGN ($5), and offers leverage of up to 1:1000.
 
Pros and Cons



PROS
CONS


There are low minimum deposit requirements
There are limited base currencies offered


HF Markets is extremely well-regulated



There is an excellent choice between trading accounts



Nigerians can get leverage up to 1:1000



Nigerians can register an NGN account




 
FXTM
Overview
Trading foreign exchange (Forex) with FXTM, a worldwide MT4/MT5 forex broker, gives traders access to a vast variety of markets throughout the world. 
FXTM, also known as ForexTime, provides its Nigerian customers with competitive spreads, lightning-fast trade execution, and in-depth currency market education.
 
Pros and Cons



PROS
CONS


FXTM is one of the best options for beginners
